 According to a couple, the Thelle Mogoerane Regional lost their baby's remains. The parents say they were shown someone else's baby at the mortuary. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A couple in Vereeniging wants the Thelle Mogoerane Regional Hospital to pay for alleged negligence. This after the family struggled to get the remains of their baby boy. The parents say they were shown someone else's baby at the mortuary. Meanwhile, the hospital says it's investigating the matter. The South African Human Rights Commission said it will be taking further steps. * eNCA's Nqobile Madlala reports.